===Etymology 2===
The genitive/dative/locative marker for ''i''-declension is identical with the {{m|xcl|-ի-}} stem vowel. In Godel's words, the remaining stem, standing in contrast to the nominative/accusative singular (which lost its stem), was apt to function as a full-fledged case form. According to Godel, in the case of the ''i-a''-declension we are dealing with a Proto-Armenian morphological innovation: the new morpheme was abstracted from the genitive/dative/locative case ending {{m|xcl|-ի}} of ''i''-stem nouns and applied to ''a''-stem nouns, whose original endings had been lost.

