===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|xcl|ira}}; compare {{cog|xpr|-𐭊𐭓𐭕|ts=-kirt/, /-gird}}, {{cog|pal|𐭪𐭫𐭲|ts=-kirt/, /-gird}}, and see there for more.<ref>{{R:xcl:AG|pages=168–172}}</ref><ref>{{R:xcl:HAB|կերտ|vol=II|pages=579–580}}</ref><ref name=Olsen>{{R:xcl:Olsen|pages=263–266}}</ref> Found also in several wholly-borrowed terms (see in the Related terms section). In Armenian, the same etymon functions also as a noun {{m|xcl|կերտ|t=building, construction}} and a verb {{m|xcl|կերտեմ|t=to make, construct}}, but these are not attested at an early date, therefore Armenian words ending in {{m|xcl||-կերտ}} are not genuine compounds from a synchronic point of view.<ref name=Olsen/>

